answers.answer: Not sure - dhea can be low for unexplained reasons.  It does seem to be lower in patients with autoimmune disease such as Lupus and also in diabetes patients.  But most often, it is for unclear reasons.

question: Hi, My serum dhea is 10, my free testosterone is low, progesterone a little low, esteriol within normal range.  My cortisol is normal but toward the higher end of normal.  I have celiac disease.  I have multiple food allergies, fatigue, etc.  What factors lower and increase dhea.  Why would dhea be as low as mine?  Thanks.
title: DHEA level
